"We are having a loud party."

74
00:06:28,923 --> 00:06:30,841
Mr Bristow...

75
00:06:30,925 --> 00:06:33,719
Sydney doesn't give a damn
what my opinion is.

76
00:06:33,802 --> 00:06:36,388
What interests me is that you do.

77
00:06:36,472 --> 00:06:40,351
It's just a custom to call
the father, that's all this is.

78
00:06:40,434 --> 00:06:44,939
I'll tell you what. I may become
your father-in-law, that's fine,

79
00:06:45,022 --> 00:06:50,110
but I will not be used as a charming
anecdote you tell your friends,

80
00:06:50,194 --> 00:06:54,782
so they can see what a quaint
old-fashioned guy Danny really is.

81
00:06:56,075 --> 00:06:58,369
Are we clear?

82
00:06:58,452 --> 00:07:00,246
Yes, sir.

83
00:07:00,329 --> 00:07:02,331
Good.

84
00:07:02,414 --> 00:07:04,833
Then welcome to the family.

85
00:07:39,577 --> 00:07:41,328
You're in late.

86
